the first page of this charm designs book for jewelers

Written in the same neat script as the cover of this charm designs book are the words "Table of Contents" at the top of the first page. Divided into two columns below in tiny print you see this list: "acacia, acorn, amaryllis, anchor, ankh, baroque, barrel, beehive, berry, bi-cone, boat, butterfly, candy, cauldron, chrysanthemum, cicada, circular, clam, cloud, cross, crown, dragon, dragonfly, elliptical, faceted, fairy, firefly, flat, fleur-de-lis, frog, gorath, hexagram, horseshoe, lantern, leaf, lily, lotus, moon, mushroom, nugget, octogram, octopus, pegasus, pentacle, pillow, pistol, quill, rectangular, rose, round, skull, snowflake, spherical, spiral, square, star, sword, triangular, triquetra, violin, and wing."

Written in the same neat script as the cover of this charm designs book are the words "Table of Contents" at the top of the first page. Divided into two columns below in tiny print you see a list of 62 types of charms.
